---
description: Security, performance, and edge case review for Python files in this multi-tenant Flask/SQLAlchemy app
globs:
  - "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

When writing or modifying Python code, apply the review skill at `.agents/skills/python.md`.

Work through its checklist before finalising any implementation. Fix violations inline — do not leave them for the user.

Non-negotiable items:
1. Every query on a tenant-owned table must include `org_id` — missing this leaks cross-tenant data
2. Every new route needs `@requires_auth` and `@requires_org_scope`
3. No client-supplied ID fetched without `org_id` re-check (IDOR)
4. No N+1 queries — use `joinedload` or batch fetch
5. No unbounded `.all()` — paginate large result sets
